notesStmt.note: Title from title page (f. i recto).

msContents.summary: Collection of poems, some anonymous, but most with indication of authors, including L. Melosi; M. B. C.; M. A. G. (Marchese Garzoni); Claudio Achillini; Angelo Tara[c]chia; Giov. Battista Vidali; [Pietro ?] Gabrielli; [Enrico?] Vialardi, etc.

supportDesc.extent: 100 leaves : 195 x 145 (145 x 70) mm. bound to 195 x 152 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, 100; [i], 1-23, 48-120, [121-123]; contemporary foliation in ink, modern foliation in pencil, upper right recto. Folios 11-23 blank, 24-47 removed, 48-71 blank, 121-123 blank.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a cursive script by two or more hands.

binding.p: Contemporary boards, with some worm damage.

origin.p: Written in Italy in the 17th century (Zacour-Hirsch).
